    • Constructor Detail

      • WatchServiceFileMonitorServiceImpl

        public WatchServiceFileMonitorServiceImpl(java.nio.file.WatchService watchService,
                                  ExecutorService executorService)
        Creates a new WatchServiceFileMonitorServiceImpl.
        Parameters:
        watchService - the watch service to use. When this argument is null, the watch service will be created during initialize() and stopped during shutdown(). If this argument is not null, then it is assumed that the watch service is running and will be closed elsewhere (for example, an IoC container)
        executorService - the executor service to use. When this argument is null, the executor service will be created during initialize() and stopped during shutdown(). If this argument is not null, then it is assumed that the executor service is running and will be closed elsewhere (for example, in an IoC container)
